  <span id="freeText4416412498355566168" style="display:none">When snarky estate agent, Dory, is summoned to the remote Welsh borders, where her mother has been taken into hospital...there's a mysterious third person living in the cottage. With author moher Vida unable to speak..who is this seemingly kindly "companion"- the rather "new age" Rhiannon? We, the readers, are privy to exerpts of Vida's secret journal, alongside the current events...<br />While I thought the author did a fair job with the fractured mother-daughter relationsahip, I'm not too struck on psychopaths and spirit animals....But it's much better than Barbara Erskin's truly dire "Sleepers Castle"...which is on vaguely similar lines...<br />*2.5</span>
