<div id="review_1541441432" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1541441432" />
    <a title="Kate Innes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49635906-kate-innes"><img alt="Kate Innes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1526123867p2/49635906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1541441432?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kate Innes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kate Innes" href="/user/show/49635906-kate-innes">Kate Innes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1541441432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16943105297397607656">I enjoyed this book in the same way that I enjoy a night-time walk. It made me more alert, it heightened my senses and made me think in new ways about what I do as a writer. The characters were vivid and believable. At times I wondered about the device of the journal, whether it was really convincing, but it, and the rest of the book, is so well written that I abandoned my doubts well before the end. I would certainly recommend it, especially to people who like high-tension, well characterised p</span>
  <span id="freeText16943105297397607656" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book in the same way that I enjoy a night-time walk. It made me more alert, it heightened my senses and made me think in new ways about what I do as a writer. The characters were vivid and believable. At times I wondered about the device of the journal, whether it was really convincing, but it, and the rest of the book, is so well written that I abandoned my doubts well before the end. I would certainly recommend it, especially to people who like high-tension, well characterised psychological stories.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16943105297397607656" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
