<div id="review_1170714688" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1170714688" />
    <a title="Suzanna Williams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6857946-suzanna-williams"><img alt="Suzanna Williams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1346613926p2/6857946.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1170714688?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzanna Williams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzanna Williams" href="/user/show/6857946-suzanna-williams">Suzanna Williams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1170714688" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15252382098748226758">How did once successful author, Vida Tremayne, end up catatonic in hospital? From the very first chapter, you just have to know.<br/><br/>Vincent presents us with an unforgettable cast of very real (and horribly dysfunctional) characters in this masterfully written tale. Despite being set in the gentle backwaters of the Shropshire borderland, the plot unfolds at a deceptively brisk pace. All of the settings, from Vida’s lonely cottage to the sleepy nearby town and the rolling hillside of the final showdow</span>
  <span id="freeText15252382098748226758" style="display:none">How did once successful author, Vida Tremayne, end up catatonic in hospital? From the very first chapter, you just have to know.<br /><br />Vincent presents us with an unforgettable cast of very real (and horribly dysfunctional) characters in this masterfully written tale. Despite being set in the gentle backwaters of the Shropshire borderland, the plot unfolds at a deceptively brisk pace. All of the settings, from Vida’s lonely cottage to the sleepy nearby town and the rolling hillside of the final showdown, are so realistic you’ll believe you’ve been there and I loved how the story, told from Vida’s daughter’s point of view, was cleverly mixed with diary extracts. <br /><br />It’s not often you can’t predict the ending of a book. No spoilers here but suffice to say The Testament of Vida Tremayne reaches a satisfying conclusion. <br /><br />Highly recommended, spine-chilling read from a brilliant author.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15252382098748226758" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


